### [2 Kings (2 Samuel) Chapter 2](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#001.md)

[2 Kings (2 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa2 2:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa2 2:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#001.md), David, by God's direction,
with his company goes up to Hebron, where he is made king of Judah; [Sa2
2:5](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#005.md), He commends them of Jabesh-gilead
for their kindness to Saul; [Sa2 2:8](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#008.md),
Abner makes Ishbosheth king of Israel; [Sa2
2:12](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#012.md), A mortal skirmish between twelve
of Abner's and twelve of Joab's men; [Sa2
2:18](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#018.md), Asahel is slain; [Sa2
2:25](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#025.md), At Abner's motion, Joab sounds a
retreat; [Sa2 2:32](../../../bib/kjv/sa2002.htm#032.md), Asahel's burial.

